modules.description: Generates integers and floating-point numbers by sampling random byte vectors and interpreting them according to specified bit widths and endianness. It supports conversions to int8, int16, int32, int64, int, and float types. Use it to create deterministic random values for cryptographic key generation or simulation scenarios requiring controlled randomness.

Generates random signed 8-bit and 16-bit integers, as well as 32-bit, 64-bit, and native integers, and floating-point numbers from a byte generator. Accepts a bound parameter to limit the range of integer and float outputs. Converts raw byte data into specific numeric types for direct use in applications requiring controlled random values.
